Created in 2015 in a technology disruption group, Powertalent is a Portuguese company specializing in TI projects.

Our experience allows us to succeed where others fail. We offer consulting solutions tailored to your real needs, we perform cyber security assessments and diagnostics and design with you the best solution. Additionally, and taking advantage of our country's strengths, such as our climate, gastronomy, and security, we provide nearshoring services, enhancing your growth. If you prefer, we also offer the service, a turnkey project, so you don't have to worry about anything else.

We are a company of people, for people!

About the job:


Create and implement game logic and AI systems for online casino games, ensuring high-quality gameplay and user experience;
Develop mathematical models to ensure fairness and unpredictability;
Write clean, efficient code to enhance performance and scalability;
Tackle and resolve technical challenges related to game logic and AI;
Collaborate closely with designers and developers to seamlessly integrate advanced game functionalities;
Analyze gameplay data to improve AI algorithms and player experience;
Optimize AI performance for different platforms and devices;
Continuously enhance our development tools and innovatively address challenges with advanced algorithms;
Explore new technologies and approaches to keep our gaming solutions at the cutting edge;
Engage in research to explore innovative AI techniques and integrate them into the games;
Work closely with other stakeholders to understand player needs and incorporate feedback into game logic;
Manage projects independently, ensuring timely completion



Requirements


Master's or Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Math, Engineering, or a related field;
At least 2 years of professional experience;
Experience with Git;
Ability to write clean, efficient, and maintainable Python code.
Familiarity with data structures, algorithms, and software engineering best practices
Good understanding of programming paradigms, such as OOP and functional programming;
Strong understanding of probability, statistics, combinatorics, and general mathematical principles related to game design and mechanics;
Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills;
Effective at teamwork and highly self-motivated with strong independence;
Meticulous attention to detail to ensure the accuracy and efficiency of game logic and AI;
Familiarity with Agile methodologies;
Fluency in Portuguese and strong verbal and written communication skills in English;
Based in or near Porto, Portugal, with a preference for in-office collaboration



Benefits


Effective contract
Food subsidy
Health insurance
Hybrid work
Continuing education and professional development
